30/08/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Defence Minister Berislav Roncevic reiterated on Wednesday (August 29th) that Croatia expects an invitation to join NATO next year. 
He met in Zagreb with German counterpart Franz Josef Jung, who said Croatia deserves to be a member of the Alliance. 
He also praised ongoing defence reforms and the participation of about 200 Croatian troops in NATO's mission in Afghanistan. 
(Makfax - 30/08/07; HRT - 29/08/07)
